      {
        "id": 9686,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Battler",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png",
        "created_at": "2006-04-27T23:32:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<h1><a name=\"p-9686-blba-2-credits-manager-version-100b-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-9686-blba-2-credits-manager-version-100b-1\"></a><span class=\"bbcode-b\">LBA 2 Credits Manager version 1.0.0</span></h1>\n<p>Current features:<br>\n- Viewing and editing the credits text;<br>\n- Exporting and replacing item;<br>\n- Saving with compression.</p>\n<p>Things to do:<br>\n- Making the compression optional;<br>\n- Viewing the shading palette image;<br>\n- Better looking credits text view/edit area with WYSIWYG features.</p>\n<p>How this program works<br>\n----------------------<br>\nYou have to load either the LBA2.HQR file or an external version of its only item. The latter is recommended, due to Visual Basics slow decompression speed. However, once the thing is loaded, youll see a tree of 3 items: credits text, shading palette and character blocks. The last item can be expanded, it will spawn an indexed list of character blocks. Each of them can be expaned as well, to show one model and two anims.</p>\n<p>The operations you can perform on these items are:<br>\n- View/Edit: for the credits text only - makes you able to view and edit it;<br>\n- Extract: extracts the selected item;<br>\n- Replace: replaces the selected item with an external item of the same type.</p>\n<p>Credits<br>\n-------<br>\nMe (OBrasilo): for initial LBA2.HQR only item specification and programming.<br>\nAlexandre Fontoura (alexfont): for help on the LBA2.HQR only item contents.</p>\n<h2><a name=\"p-9686-links-2\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-9686-links-2\"></a>Links</h2>\n<p>The program: <a href=\"http://www.obrasilero.com/LBA2Edit.zip\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">http://www.obrasilero.com/LBA2Edit.zip</a>.<br>\nThe source code: <a href=\"http://www.obrasilero.com/LBA2Edit-source.zip\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">http://www.obrasilero.com/LBA2Edit-source.zip</a>.</p>\n<p>Screenshot<br>\n-----------<br>\n<span alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" class=\"broken-image\" title=\"This image is broken\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-unlink svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#unlink\"></use></svg></span></p>\n<p>I hope youll find the program useful. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
